						<summary>

						<p>This is an incomplete inscription. It records a sale of seven <hi rend="italic">mā</hi> of land irrigated by the ‘western tank’ with exemption of taxes, by the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of Uṟumūr a <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> and <hi rend="italic">brahmadēya</hi> of Nalvayalūr-kūṟṟam on the north bank (of the river) for 10 <hi rend="italic">kaḻanju</hi> of gold received by them from the temple of <hi rend="bold">Śiru-Tirukkōyil-Perumānaḍigaḻ.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
